## jq — JSON Processing

```bash
# Pretty-print JSON
cat file.json | jq '.'

# Extract a field
cat file.json | jq '.key.subkey'

# Filter arrays
cat file.json | jq '.items[] | select(.status == "failed")'

# Count items
cat file.json | jq '.items | length'

# Transform output
cat file.json | jq -r '.items[] | "\(.name)\t\(.status)"'

# Docker inspect with jq
ssh ocean 'docker inspect plex' | jq '.[0].State'
ssh ocean 'docker inspect plex' | jq '.[0].NetworkSettings.Ports'

# Prometheus API with jq
curl -s 'http://192.168.1.143:9090/api/v1/targets' | jq '.data.activeTargets[] | select(.health != "up") | .labels.job'

# GitHub API with jq
gh api repos/bluefishforsale/homelab/actions/runs --jq '.workflow_runs[:5] | .[] | "\(.name) \(.conclusion) \(.created_at)"'
```

